</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="93" pageNumber="693" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="93.[1353,2561,302,1155]" pageId="93" pageNumber="693">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1356,1704,923,957]" pageId="93" pageNumber="693">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Highland Mosaic-tailed Rat has a relatively wide distribution and there seem to be 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rummler" authorityYear="1935" box="[2433,2561,962,996]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Macruromys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="93" pageNumber="733" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">no major</taxonomicName>
threats to this relatively common species, but further research is needed in order fully to understand its natural history and evolution, and any potential threats facing it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
